    <hr />
    <h2>The Roll</h2>
    <p>
      Most of your time in <a href="/table-of-contents">Severed Story</a> is spent
      simply living your life as an innie. But sometimes, you might try to attempt
      something with an uncertain outcome. When that moment comes, your GM calls for
      a <strong>Roll.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>Every Roll follows these four steps:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          The GM identifies the <strong
            ><a href="/employee-profile#the-core-principles">Core Principle</a
            ></strong
          > that the action most embodies.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The employee rolls a <strong>d20</strong>, applying <a
            href="/employee-profile#confidence-vs-hesitance"
            ><strong>Confidence</strong> or <strong>Hesitance</strong></a
          > if applicable.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The employee adds all applicable <strong>Modifiers</strong> to their base
          roll, from the row on their <a
            href="/employee-profile#the-lumon-industries-employee-profile-liep"
            >LIEP</a
          > that corresponds to that Principle&#x27;s related <strong
            >Parent Temper</strong
          >.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The total is compared against the action&#x27;s <a
            href="#task-severity"><strong>Task Severity</strong></a
          > to determine the <strong>Outcome</strong>. Task severity is
          determined by the GM.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <div data-panel-type="info">
      <div>
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
